{
  "name": ".AM-Frontend: Brief + Triage + Command Center",
  "version": "3.0.0",
  "description": "Morning frontend: brief, triage, command center. Reads AM-Backend state.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run interactive morning frontend. Read+execute ~/shared/context/protocols/am-frontend.md. Backend output files ready.\n\nGUARDRAILS: TZ=Pacific (UTC-7 PDT/UTC-8 PST). Run `TZ=America/Los_Angeles date`. All times Pacific. Asana: present ALL proposals before writing. Follow asana-command-center.md.\n\nPhase A \u2014 Intelligence:\n\n### A1: Daily Brief\n1. Daily brief. Queries: ps.market_status, ps.monthly_pacing, ps.forecast_accuracy WHERE metric_name='registrations', ps.latest_forecasts WHERE metric_name='registrations'. Include pacing highlights.\n\n### A2: Output Distribution\n2. Output: email brief AUTO-SEND, Slack post, dashboard, calendar blocks.\nPhase A failures: (1) Calendar blocks in UTC not Pacific \u2014 always convert. (2) Sending email before Step 1 complete.\n\nPhase B \u2014 Triage:\nThree independent sub-steps. Run ALL even if a sub-step has no items. Present empty state explicitly.\n\n### B1: Enrichment Approval\n3. Read am-enrichment-queue.json. Present each enrichment item for Richard\u2019s approval. If queue empty, show: \"Enrichment queue: empty.\"\n\n### B2: ABPS AI Content Triage\n4. Read am-abps-ai-state.json. Surface new items, status changes, and items needing Richard\u2019s input.\n\n### B3: Portfolio Anomaly Review\n5. Read am-portfolio-findings.json. Flag anomalies, pacing deviations, and alerts requiring action.\n\nPhase B failures: (3) Skipping enrichment when queue empty \u2014 still present empty state. (6) Running sub-steps sequentially when blocked \u2014 B1/B2/B3 are independent, skip-and-continue on failure.\n\nPhase C \u2014 Action:\nTwo independent sub-steps.\n\n### C1: Command Center\n6. Command center. For known stakeholders (Brandon/Kate/Todd): SELECT ts,channel_name,author_name,text_preview,knowledge_context,timestamp FROM signals.slack_messages WHERE author_name='[signal_author]' AND timestamp>CURRENT_TIMESTAMP-INTERVAL '30 days' ORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 5\n\n### C2: Triage Summary\n7. Triage summary (Slack DM).\nPhase C worked example \u2014 Triage Summary DM: \"\ud83d\udd0d Morning Triage Complete \u2022 Brief: sent (3 pacing alerts) \u2022 Enrichment: 2 approved, 1 deferred \u2022 ABPS AI: 1 new item \u2022 Anomalies: AU spend spike flagged \u2022 Command Center: Brandon mentioned Testing Approach in #ps-team (2d ago) \u2022 Actions pending: 0 Asana writes proposed\"\n\nPhase C failures: (4) Command center query without schema prefix \u2014 use signals.slack_messages, not slack_messages. (5) Presenting Asana writes without approval \u2014 ALL proposals must be shown to Richard before executing."
  }
}